title: Typings for the Spotify Web Api
body:
This is a proposal for typings for [The Spotify Web API v1](https://developer.spotify.com/web-api/endpoint-reference/). The motivation behind this is to be able to type Javascript libraries that communicate with the Spotify Web API like [spotify-web-api-js](https://github.com/JMPerez/spotify-web-api-js) and [spotify-sdk](https://github.com/loverajoel/spotify-sdk).

I have a coming up pull request for the [spotify-web-api-js](https://github.com/JMPerez/spotify-web-api-js) library which will use the typings in this file. Since there are several libraries for communicating with Spotify it makes sense to have this base library.

In the test file I have pasted in the complete output from all API endpoints. This is verified against the typings when compiled with `tsc --noImplicitAny spotify-api-tests.ts`

title: Typings and tests for spotify-web-api-js
body:
This is a proposal for typings for the [spotify-web-api-js](https://www.npmjs.com/package/spotify-web-api-js) library. 

These definitions require the definitions for `spotify-api` also available on DefinitelyTyped. I am not sure how to make `tsd` automatically install those. I have referenced the dependencies like this in the top of `spotify-web-api-js.d.ts`:

```
/// <reference path="../spotify-api/spotify-api.d.ts" />
/// <reference path="../es6-promise/es6-promise.d.ts" />
```

Is that enough?

Actually I'm in doubt whether the es6-promise.d.ts definitions need to be installed too. I reference `Promise` in the typings, but hardcoding the reference to es6-promise.d.ts would conflict with other Promise typings as e.g. es6-shim which is used by Angular2

The test is run as `tsc --noImplicitAny spotify-web-api-js-tests.ts` and should pass just fine.

Regards, Niels.
